                <head>114. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The meeting of the Ministerial Council of the Organization for Economic
                    Cooperation and Development was held in Paris November 25–26, 1965. Under
                    Secretary of State for Economic Affairs <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Thomas C.
                        Mann</persName> headed the U.S. Delegation, which included <gloss
                        target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> Administrator <persName corresp="#p_BDE1">David
                        E. Bell</persName> and Assistant Secretary of State for Economic Affairs
                        <persName corresp="#p_SAM4">Anthony M. Solomon</persName>. For a full list
                    of the U.S. Delegation, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                    December 27, 1965, page 1039. Text of the communique, November 26, is ibid.,
                    pages 1038–1039. Documentation on the meeting is in Washington National Records
                    Center, RG 286, <gloss target="#t_DAC1">DAC</gloss> Material: FRC 70 <gloss
                        target="#t_A1">A</gloss> 5922, Meetings—<gloss target="#t_OECD1"
                        >OECD</gloss> Ministerial Meeting November 25–26, 1965; and Department of
                    State, Conference Files: Lot 66 <gloss target="#t_D1">D</gloss> 347, CF
                    2564–2565.</p>
            </div>
